{
  "$comment": "Mateu <-> Figma design contract. SINGLE SOURCE OF TRUTH for the design-to-code pipeline: the Figma plugin (design/figma/plugin) BUILDS the component library from this file, and modux's Figma importer maps instances found in a Figma file BACK through it to UiComponentNodeEntity trees (kind + params) that the generators emit as Java/C#/Python. Conventions: component names are 'Mateu/<Category>/<Name>'; 'variants' become Figma VARIANT axes (visual), 'props' become Figma component properties (TEXT/BOOLEAN, non-visual config like actionId), 'texts' name the text layers whose content is a designer override that maps to the given param. 'sketch' is the compact draw spec the plugin renders (primitives: title, label, value, text, chip, fieldbox, hr, dot, bullets, bar, stepper, row, table, imagebox, button, tile).",
  "version": 1,
  "namePrefix": "Mateu/",
  "lumo": {
    "primary": "#1a73e8",
    "base": "#ffffff",
    "body": "#1a1a1a",
    "secondary": "#666666",
    "contrast10": "#e8e8e8",
    "contrast20": "#d0d0d0",
    "radiusM": 8,
    "radiusL": 12,
